<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110526055244/http://www.dafdigest.org/shekalim/Shekalim%20006.pdf">"Tzedaka and Maaser Kesafim"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>dafdigest.org</i>. Chicago Center for Torah and Chesed. May 23, 2006. Number 449. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.dafdigest.org/shekalim/Shekalim%20006.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on May 26, 2011<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">February 3,</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=dafdigest.org&amp;rft.atitle=Tzedaka+and+Maaser+Kesafim&amp;rft.pages=Number+449&amp;rft.date=2006-05-23&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dafdigest.org%2Fshekalim%2FShekalim%2520006.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATithes+in+Judaism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
